Question_Text: Right now, your stress level 1–10?
Where in your body do you feel tension first today?
When criticized, do you defend, explain, freeze, or get curious? (choose one)
Under stress, what is your default control move (micromanage, overwork, withdraw, criticize)?
In conflict, do you pursue or withdraw? Which is default?
What behavior in others irritates you instantly?
What do you call ‘high standards’ that is actually fear of being judged?
What fear do you disguise as logic this week?
Who can tell you hard truths without you punishing them? (name one)
If you had to name your ego defense (humor/intellect/anger/withdrawal), what is it?
Where do you demand certainty you cannot get (people’s loyalty, outcomes, respect)?
What trait you dislike in others do you fear exists in you?
When you apologize, is it repair or reputation management?
What behavior reduces trust even if it increases speed (interrupting, dismissing, nitpicking)?
What do you envy in others (ease, freedom, love, creativity)? Choose one.
What belief about vulnerability would you like to retire?
What boundary do you set too late (or not at all)?
Under stress, what do you ‘optimize’ to avoid feeling (metrics, tasks, people)?
What part of you is exiled (play/rest/softness) because it feels unsafe?
Do you confuse being right with being safe? (yes/no + one example)
What is one habit you use as self-punishment disguised as discipline?
Who is your safe person for repair? What makes it safe?
What’s the 5% truer sentence about your ego pattern that you avoid writing?
What is your default shame response: attack, explain, withdraw, or perform?
What’s one situation where you will say ‘I don’t know’ without compensating?
Write a 1-sentence repair opener you can use after conflict.
Name one behavior you will stop doing this week under stress.
Name 2 strengths you keep even under stress (your toolkit).
Pick one regulation tool to deploy before a hard conversation (walk/water/breath/pause).
Name your current bottleneck: Hardware, OS, Network, or Output. (Pick one.)
